  "text": "14,15 Isolation outcome was defined to be successful when total islet yield was more than 250,000 IEQ per pancreas. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Product release criteria for clinical islet transplantation were !5,000 IEQ per kg recipient's body weight, viability of !70%, purity of !30%, packed tissue volume of 7 mL, stimulation index of !1.0, endotoxin of 5 EU/kg, and the absence of bacterial contaminations determined as gram negative stain. [CITATION_3] Posttransplant function of islets transplanted into patients with type 1 diabetes mellitus was assessed by selfmonitoring of blood glucose levels and documentation of insulin requirements. Plasma C-peptide levels and HbA1c were measured at follow-up visits 3 and 6 mo after transplantation utilizing standard methods. [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] The C-peptide to glucose ratio was calculated as described by Faradji et al. [CITATION_6] ",
